1
00:00:05,866 --> 00:00:07,766
[theme song]

2
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:40,000
[birds calling]

3
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:40,933
A secret sauce?

4
00:01:41,033 --> 00:01:41,633
When's it ready?

5
00:01:41,733 --> 00:01:43,000
Can I taste it?

6
00:01:45,766 --> 00:01:46,933
Would you quit jumping around?

7
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:49,600
Can't you see that I'm
trying to work here?

8
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,400
I just hope Father
doesn't find out

9
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:56,233
I borrowed his special little
recipe, or I'm in big trouble.

10
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:16,033
[grunting]

11
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:18,466
Well, I guess this is it.

12
00:02:18,566 --> 00:02:21,033
Time to test my secret sauce.

13
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:23,633
This secret
okonomiyaki sauce has

14
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:25,700
been aging for the last decade.

15
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,933
The moment of truth has arrived.

16
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:50,833
RANMA (VOICEOVER): Ukyo's
Secret Sauce, Part One.

17
00:02:50,933 --> 00:02:54,100
[clock chiming]

18
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,300
I wonder what was
wrong with Ukyo.

19
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,233
She's never missed a
day of school before.

20
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:58,900
I don't know.

21
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,533
Maybe she got sick.

22
00:03:05,266 --> 00:03:07,833
You're saying you're depressed
because you ruined some sauce?

23
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:10,466
You mean you skipped
school for that?

24
00:03:10,566 --> 00:03:13,166
Ukyo!

25
00:03:13,266 --> 00:03:16,033
Hmm?

26
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:17,033
Care for a taste?

27
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:21,300
It's disgusting!

28
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,466
How could I have
failed like this

29
00:03:26,566 --> 00:03:30,600
after devoting my entire
life to making okonomiyaki?

30
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:35,333
I still remember
the day I made it.

31
00:03:35,433 --> 00:03:36,566
There!

32
00:03:36,666 --> 00:03:39,100
Now all we have to do is
let it cure for a few years.

33
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:42,400
[laughing]

34
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:47,166
I don't understand
what went wrong.

35
00:03:47,266 --> 00:03:51,100
I'm positive I followed my
father's recipe exactly.

36
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,933
Ranma, honey, do you
remember if I made

37
00:03:54,033 --> 00:03:55,633
sure the lid was sealed tight?

38
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:58,133
Yeah, I'm pretty sure it was.

39
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:01,700
So you're saying this is the
same sauce from back then?

40
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:04,166
[sigh]

41
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:14,400
I want to get a little taste.

42
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,400
[scream]

43
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,266
Oh, I really did it now!

44
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:31,533
A little of this, and this,
and some of this, and, oh!

45
00:04:31,633 --> 00:04:33,733
RANMA (VOICEOVER):
[laughing] Man,

46
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:37,600
if Ukyo ever found out what
really happened, I'd be toast.

47
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,200
Oh, don't worry.

48
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:43,166
I think you should just calm
down and have some porridge.

49
00:04:43,266 --> 00:04:44,666
I just made it.

50
00:04:44,766 --> 00:04:45,700
You made it?

51
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,300
Are you-- are you
trying to kill her?

52
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,066
Oh, thank you, Akane.

53
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:53,566
I will have some.

54
00:04:53,666 --> 00:04:56,066
[groaning]

55
00:05:03,266 --> 00:05:03,707
Ukyo!

56
00:05:08,966 --> 00:05:10,400
Because you live
on your own, Ukyo,

57
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,833
I think it's in
your best interest

58
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:13,700
to stay with us for a while.

59
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:17,733
At least until you
feel well again.

60
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:21,366
Thank you so much for the kind
offer, but it's not that bad.

61
00:05:21,466 --> 00:05:21,933
Hold on.

62
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:23,300
Uh-uh.

63
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,933
Not only are you suffering from
the psychological distress,

64
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:28,500
but you ate Akane's food.

65
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,966
[groaning]

66
00:05:30,066 --> 00:05:31,433
Hey!

67
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:34,033
Don't worry about it, Akane.

68
00:05:34,133 --> 00:05:35,566
I'm sure I'll feel better soon.

69
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:37,100
I'm so sorry.

70
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,766
Hey, and-- and if you need
anything, you can just ask.

71
00:05:39,866 --> 00:05:40,307
Huh?

72
00:05:40,366 --> 00:05:41,366
Ranma?

73
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:44,600
How come you're suddenly
being so nice to me?

74
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:46,900
Uh, no reason.

75
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,666
No reason at all.

76
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:53,100
Why do you ask, anyway?

77
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,533
Come on, Ukyo.

78
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:58,466
We've been friends for
a long time, right?

79
00:05:58,566 --> 00:06:00,433
[growling]

80
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:00,974
Saotome.

81
00:06:03,566 --> 00:06:07,233
Well, if I'm going to
stay, will you help?

82
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:09,433
And I think that
should go over there.

83
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:10,200
Sure.

84
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,866
Is that all her junk?

85
00:06:11,966 --> 00:06:15,266
So is she moving in here?

86
00:06:15,366 --> 00:06:18,233
Ukyo, are you planning on
moving into Ranma's room?

87
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:19,433
Of course not.

88
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:21,166
I'm only going to
stay until I get out

89
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:24,333
of this depression from
ruining that sauce.

90
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,733
Ranma, are you OK?

91
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,100
Uh, yeah, sure.

92
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,500
Um, I'm fine.

93
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,566
[laughing]

94
00:06:30,666 --> 00:06:33,966
Hey, Ranma, are you trying
to hide something from us?

95
00:06:34,066 --> 00:06:36,033
[crash]

96
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:37,700
So now what are
you going to do?

97
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,433
About what?

98
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:42,966
And why is it you're suddenly
being so nice to Ukyo?

99
00:06:43,066 --> 00:06:45,700
I don't know what you're
talking about, Akane.

100
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,233
I am starting to smell a rat.

101
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:49,900
Are you sure there
isn't something

102
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,066
you're not telling me?

103
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:51,766
Huh, Ranma?

104
00:06:51,866 --> 00:06:52,966
Yeah.

105
00:06:53,066 --> 00:06:56,166
Now, would you quit asking
me so many questions?

106
00:06:56,266 --> 00:07:00,033
Are you sure about that?

107
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:04,366
Anyway, it's kind of hard
to explain the relationship

108
00:07:04,466 --> 00:07:06,333
between me and Ukyo.

109
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:07,866
You wouldn't understand.

110
00:07:07,966 --> 00:07:10,200
Huh?

111
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:13,533
Oh, man, I never thought
Ukyo would get so depressed

112
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:16,633
over stupid sauce.

113
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:19,600
I've got to think
a way out of this.

114
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:23,400
Ranma, honey, want
me to scrub your back?

115
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:28,233
I can't just stay here and lie
around doing nothing at all.

116
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:30,266
[gurgle]

117
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:32,400
OK, sit up, Ranma, honey.

118
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,200
[whimpering]

119
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:36,400
How come so shy?

120
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:37,866
Come on, we grew up together.

121
00:07:37,966 --> 00:07:40,066
Well, uh, you know, I, uh--

122
00:07:40,166 --> 00:07:41,500
Huh?

123
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,866
[growling]

124
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:52,533
Man.

125
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:54,400
Why won't Akane ever
listen to what I

126
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,900
have to say before she hits me?

127
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:00,333
Huh?

128
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:01,200
Ranma honey.

129
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:04,200
I've been waiting for you.

130
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:07,233
It'll be just like when we were
little kids, sleeping together

131
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,100
when we were camping.

132
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,966
Uh, I think I'd better not.

133
00:08:11,066 --> 00:08:12,500
What are you waiting for?

134
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,766
And please, don't tell
me that you're shy again.

135
00:08:15,866 --> 00:08:18,000
This-- this is not good.

136
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:20,466
[screaming]

137
00:08:20,566 --> 00:08:23,200
Hey, I didn't do
anything, Akane!

138
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:25,833
But you were going
to, weren't you?

139
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:30,900
--[laughing] Well, now, Ranma,
for a person who's living

140
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,966
in his fiancee's house for
free, what are you thinking?

141
00:08:34,066 --> 00:08:36,400
But it's not what
it looks like!

142
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:49,133
[growling]

143
00:08:50,266 --> 00:08:52,733
I don't care if they
are just friends!

144
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:56,700
It just isn't right having
a girl sleep in his room!

145
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,833
Why you--

146
00:08:57,933 --> 00:08:59,733
[shouting]

147
00:09:02,666 --> 00:09:05,433
[scream]

148
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:06,966
Now what?

149
00:09:07,066 --> 00:09:08,900
Don't tell me you
slept up in the tree.

150
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,833
Yeah.

151
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:11,700
And to think that
Ukyo's probably

152
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:15,500
all nice and comfortable,
all snuggled up in my bed.

153
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,933
If you keep this up, you're
going to catch a cold.

154
00:09:18,033 --> 00:09:21,666
Well, I can't do anything about
it until Ukyo feels better.

155
00:09:21,766 --> 00:09:24,033
So when do you think
Ukyo will leave?

156
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:27,500
You listening?

157
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:37,266
[gagging]

158
00:09:37,366 --> 00:09:38,833
What is that smell?

159
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:39,866
Oh, it reeks!

160
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:44,966
What is going on out here?

161
00:09:45,066 --> 00:09:46,900
[growl]

162
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,900
I hope you don't
mind, but I thought

163
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,400
I'd make breakfast for myself.

164
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:56,000
Even if it is a mistake
I made a long time ago,

165
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:59,000
you all have to understand,
I still have my pride.

166
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:05,133
And while everyone might
think this sauce is revolting,

167
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:07,700
I still have got to eat it.

168
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:12,100
I've never witnessed
anything quite so brave.

169
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,066
Hey, don't do it!

170
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:16,700
Ukyo!

171
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,533
Ranma, honey.

172
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:19,766
Ranma?

173
00:10:19,866 --> 00:10:20,600
Ranma?

174
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,233
[growling]

175
00:10:29,866 --> 00:10:30,966
Delicious.

176
00:10:31,066 --> 00:10:32,333
Oh, no!

177
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:34,433
Ranma, honey!

178
00:10:34,533 --> 00:10:35,933
Ranma, are you OK?

179
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:38,400
I'll go make him a bed.

180
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,366
Oh, brother.

181
00:10:57,414 --> 00:10:59,247
So, Ranma, what
happened to your face?

182
00:10:59,347 --> 00:11:03,314
It looks like you've been
trying Akane's cooking again.

183
00:11:03,414 --> 00:11:04,881
UKYO (VOICEOVER):
Ranma honey saved me

184
00:11:04,981 --> 00:11:06,081
from eating that okonomiyaki.

185
00:11:09,881 --> 00:11:13,481
AKANE (VOICEOVER):
Something isn't right.

186
00:11:13,581 --> 00:11:16,181
So, Akane, what do
you want to talk about?

187
00:11:16,281 --> 00:11:18,381
Um, don't you think
that Ranma's been

188
00:11:18,481 --> 00:11:20,181
acting really strange lately?

189
00:11:20,281 --> 00:11:23,414
Well, I guess
maybe a little bit.

190
00:11:23,514 --> 00:11:24,647
I thought so.

191
00:11:24,747 --> 00:11:28,014
What I can't seem to figure
out is the reason why.

192
00:11:28,114 --> 00:11:30,781
To be honest, I never
really thought about it.

193
00:11:33,747 --> 00:11:35,881
According to the
recipe, we have

194
00:11:35,981 --> 00:11:37,981
to make sure the vat
is sealed, and then we

195
00:11:38,081 --> 00:11:40,047
have to let it sit for 10 years.

196
00:11:40,147 --> 00:11:40,814
What?

197
00:11:40,914 --> 00:11:42,381
We have to wait 10 years?

198
00:11:42,481 --> 00:11:43,281
That's right.

199
00:11:43,381 --> 00:11:44,614
But don't worry.

200
00:11:44,714 --> 00:11:46,814
When it's done, I promise
you'll be the first to try it.

201
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:48,347
That is, for a price.

202
00:11:48,447 --> 00:11:50,614
Then what?

203
00:11:50,714 --> 00:11:54,314
I seem to recall making a
really important promise.

204
00:11:54,414 --> 00:11:55,981
Huh?

205
00:11:56,081 --> 00:11:57,481
OK, if it tastes good--

206
00:11:57,581 --> 00:11:58,814
Hmm?

207
00:11:58,914 --> 00:12:01,981
Then you have to promise
that you will look after me

208
00:12:02,081 --> 00:12:03,714
for the rest of my life.

209
00:12:03,814 --> 00:12:06,114
Yeah, OK.

210
00:12:06,214 --> 00:12:09,747
That must mean that Ranma
still remembers the promise

211
00:12:09,847 --> 00:12:11,714
he made to me back then.

212
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:14,181
And that's the reason why
he ate that disgusting sauce

213
00:12:14,281 --> 00:12:16,247
at breakfast.

214
00:12:16,347 --> 00:12:19,947
Because he wants to spend
the rest of his life with me!

215
00:12:20,047 --> 00:12:22,547
But I go and ruin that sauce.

216
00:12:22,647 --> 00:12:25,514
Oh, another stupid
Ranma promise.

217
00:12:29,514 --> 00:12:32,214
That's what you get
for eating that sauce.

218
00:12:32,314 --> 00:12:34,247
Oh, man, it hurts.

219
00:12:34,347 --> 00:12:38,981
Maybe that's because you
have some explaining to do.

220
00:12:39,081 --> 00:12:41,014
What do you mean?

221
00:12:41,114 --> 00:12:43,047
Like what you did
when you were little.

222
00:12:43,147 --> 00:12:45,114
Huh?

223
00:12:45,214 --> 00:12:48,081
Then-- then-- then you know?

224
00:12:48,181 --> 00:12:49,381
Then it's true.

225
00:12:49,481 --> 00:12:50,414
Hmm.

226
00:12:50,514 --> 00:12:52,881
Something I'll never
be able to forget.

227
00:12:52,981 --> 00:12:55,014
But-- but Ranma, when
you two were little,

228
00:12:55,114 --> 00:12:56,881
didn't you think Ukyo was a boy?

229
00:12:56,981 --> 00:12:57,947
So?

230
00:12:58,047 --> 00:12:59,314
What does that have
to do with anything?

231
00:12:59,414 --> 00:13:01,347
I guess that's true, but--

232
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:02,347
Listen.

233
00:13:02,447 --> 00:13:03,714
Even if it's something
that happened

234
00:13:03,814 --> 00:13:07,147
when Ukyo and I were still kids,
I still can't hurt her, OK?

235
00:13:07,247 --> 00:13:07,688
Hmm?

236
00:13:10,714 --> 00:13:12,614
[gagging]

237
00:13:15,381 --> 00:13:17,714
Ukyo.

238
00:13:17,814 --> 00:13:21,447
I have decided to
dispose of my sauce.

239
00:13:21,547 --> 00:13:23,414
[gasp]

240
00:13:23,514 --> 00:13:27,481
So please, tell me honestly
that it tastes horrible.

241
00:13:27,581 --> 00:13:30,681
Ranma, I have to put
being an okonomiyaki chef

242
00:13:30,781 --> 00:13:32,381
over my happiness.

243
00:13:32,481 --> 00:13:34,247
UKYO (VOICEOVER): And
I can leave this behind

244
00:13:34,347 --> 00:13:35,547
if I hear you say it.

245
00:13:38,881 --> 00:13:42,047
All I have to do is eat this
one last time and I'm free.

246
00:13:42,147 --> 00:13:46,714
One, two, one, two, one, two,
one, two, one, two, one, two,

247
00:13:46,814 --> 00:13:47,947
one, two, one!

248
00:14:04,381 --> 00:14:07,647
It's actually pretty tasty.

249
00:14:07,747 --> 00:14:08,647
Serious?

250
00:14:08,747 --> 00:14:11,347
You-- you really liked it?

251
00:14:11,447 --> 00:14:13,647
I'm touched!

252
00:14:13,747 --> 00:14:15,914
Ranma honey!

253
00:14:16,014 --> 00:14:17,814
[groaning]

254
00:14:20,714 --> 00:14:23,614
Well then, now you'll have
to spend the rest of your life

255
00:14:23,714 --> 00:14:24,981
with Ukyo!

256
00:14:25,081 --> 00:14:26,114
Huh?

257
00:14:26,214 --> 00:14:28,247
I'm going to have to put
my happiness over being

258
00:14:28,347 --> 00:14:30,614
an okonomiyaki chef after all!

259
00:14:30,714 --> 00:14:33,347
What in the world are
you two talking about?

260
00:14:33,447 --> 00:14:35,081
Don't play dumb, Ranma.

261
00:14:35,181 --> 00:14:35,814
But I--

262
00:14:38,414 --> 00:14:41,547
I'm so happy you remembered.

263
00:14:41,647 --> 00:14:42,714
Huh?

264
00:14:42,814 --> 00:14:46,447
When we were little
kids, the promise we made!

