OK, if it tastes
good, then you have

266
00:14:50,081 --> 00:14:52,847
to promise that you
will look after me

267
00:14:52,947 --> 00:14:54,347
for the rest of my life.

268
00:14:54,447 --> 00:14:55,314
Yeah, OK!

269
00:14:55,414 --> 00:14:58,114
[laughing]

270
00:14:58,214 --> 00:14:59,514
Huh?

271
00:14:59,614 --> 00:15:02,547
I may not be much of
a woman now, Ranma,

272
00:15:02,647 --> 00:15:04,581
but I promise to be a good wife.

273
00:15:04,681 --> 00:15:07,047
[nervous laughter] Um.

274
00:15:09,881 --> 00:15:14,247
Uh, Ukyo, are you sure we
made this promise back then?

275
00:15:14,347 --> 00:15:17,314
Ranma, honey, are you
telling me you don't remember?

276
00:15:17,414 --> 00:15:19,281
[nervous laughter]

277
00:15:19,381 --> 00:15:21,247
Is this true, Ranma?

278
00:15:26,247 --> 00:15:29,414
What a stench!

279
00:15:29,514 --> 00:15:32,314
[groaning]

280
00:15:32,414 --> 00:15:34,881
Ranma honey ate this
horrible okonomiyaki

281
00:15:34,981 --> 00:15:38,781
with the ruined sauce and
said that it tasted good!

282
00:15:38,881 --> 00:15:40,881
He couldn't have done it
if it wasn't for love!

283
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:42,481
Come back here, you
worthless little cheat!

284
00:15:42,581 --> 00:15:43,022
Come here!

285
00:15:43,081 --> 00:15:45,314
[crashing]

286
00:15:45,414 --> 00:15:47,214
Oh, my.

287
00:15:47,314 --> 00:15:51,014
This just gets
more complicated.

288
00:15:51,114 --> 00:15:52,247
Ranma, you idiot!

289
00:15:55,181 --> 00:15:58,281
Honestly, saying that
he'd take care of Ukyo

290
00:15:58,381 --> 00:16:01,147
for the rest of his life?

291
00:16:01,247 --> 00:16:02,047
Wait a minute.

292
00:16:02,147 --> 00:16:04,381
He can't be serious.

293
00:16:04,481 --> 00:16:07,181
But then again, he did remember
that promise with Ukyo.

294
00:16:10,447 --> 00:16:14,181
Ranma, if you want to keep that
promise and take care of her,

295
00:16:14,281 --> 00:16:15,147
fine!

296
00:16:15,247 --> 00:16:17,647
Ranma, honey,
Akane says it's OK.

297
00:16:17,747 --> 00:16:20,981
Well, Akane, you were still
uncute until the very end,

298
00:16:21,081 --> 00:16:22,447
weren't you?

299
00:16:22,547 --> 00:16:23,847
Good bye, Akane!

300
00:16:23,947 --> 00:16:26,314
Huh?

301
00:16:26,414 --> 00:16:28,814
Huh?

302
00:16:28,914 --> 00:16:30,281
No, Ranma, wait!

303
00:16:30,381 --> 00:16:31,781
You can't leave without me!

304
00:16:31,881 --> 00:16:32,781
I'm sorry!

305
00:16:35,847 --> 00:16:36,314
Huh?

306
00:16:36,414 --> 00:16:37,347
Wait a minute.

307
00:16:37,447 --> 00:16:39,314
I'm not the one who
should apologize!

308
00:16:39,414 --> 00:16:42,614
[screaming]

309
00:16:46,181 --> 00:16:47,647
You've got to believe me!

310
00:16:47,747 --> 00:16:48,881
I'm sorry, Mr. Tendo!

311
00:16:48,981 --> 00:16:49,914
I'm sorry!

312
00:16:50,014 --> 00:16:51,481
It's just a
misunderstanding, really!

313
00:16:51,581 --> 00:16:53,547
I-- I--

314
00:16:53,647 --> 00:16:55,881
Huh?

315
00:16:55,981 --> 00:16:59,281
Now why in the world am
I apologizing to you?

316
00:16:59,381 --> 00:17:01,114
I really don't know.

317
00:17:01,214 --> 00:17:03,047
Maybe it's because
you're a complete idiot.

318
00:17:05,847 --> 00:17:08,481
You mean you're the
one who made that sauce?

319
00:17:08,581 --> 00:17:09,681
Yeah.

320
00:17:09,781 --> 00:17:11,881
Because I was the one who
spilled the first batch.

321
00:17:11,981 --> 00:17:14,247
So what made it
taste so rotten, huh?

322
00:17:14,347 --> 00:17:17,181
It could have been either
the insect wine or maybe even

323
00:17:17,281 --> 00:17:19,447
the powdered cuttlefish.

324
00:17:19,547 --> 00:17:22,581
Then what about the
promise you made with Ukyo?

325
00:17:22,681 --> 00:17:24,047
I forgot.

326
00:17:24,147 --> 00:17:25,881
You moron!

327
00:17:25,981 --> 00:17:27,214
Don't worry about it.

328
00:17:27,314 --> 00:17:29,614
I'll just explain it
to her and apologize.

329
00:17:29,714 --> 00:17:32,314
I really hope this works.

330
00:17:32,414 --> 00:17:34,747
Man's got to take
responsibility for his actions.

331
00:17:34,847 --> 00:17:35,547
I'll do it.

332
00:17:35,647 --> 00:17:36,088
Huh?

333
00:17:43,447 --> 00:17:44,914
Ukyo, we gotta talk.

334
00:17:45,014 --> 00:17:48,547
Oh, Ranma, honey, you're
just in time for dinner!

335
00:17:48,647 --> 00:17:50,847
Huh?

336
00:17:50,947 --> 00:17:51,647
Uh.

337
00:17:51,747 --> 00:17:54,314
It'll be just the two of us.

338
00:17:54,414 --> 00:17:56,214
I'm so happy.

339
00:17:56,314 --> 00:17:58,881
The bride and her
husband to be, all alone.

340
00:17:58,981 --> 00:18:01,147
But-- but you don't understand.

341
00:18:01,247 --> 00:18:02,014
Ahh!

342
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:03,781
Ahh.

343
00:18:03,881 --> 00:18:05,214
[laughing] See?

344
00:18:05,314 --> 00:18:07,281
I'll make a good wife for you.

345
00:18:07,381 --> 00:18:09,214
[laughing]

346
00:18:09,314 --> 00:18:10,147
Ahh.

347
00:18:10,247 --> 00:18:12,547
Ahh.

348
00:18:12,647 --> 00:18:14,647
What would you
like to try next?

349
00:18:14,747 --> 00:18:17,481
Uh, how about the sauce broth?

350
00:18:17,581 --> 00:18:19,447
Ranma!

351
00:18:19,547 --> 00:18:22,247
Weren't you going
to explain things?

352
00:18:22,347 --> 00:18:24,914
Or was your little promise to
me like every other promise

353
00:18:25,014 --> 00:18:26,614
you seem to make?

354
00:18:26,714 --> 00:18:29,281
Am I sensing a conflict here?

355
00:18:29,381 --> 00:18:30,947
Remember what you told me?

356
00:18:31,047 --> 00:18:33,014
[nervous laughter] Oh, right.

357
00:18:33,114 --> 00:18:33,947
Ukyo?

358
00:18:34,047 --> 00:18:34,488
Ahh.

359
00:18:34,547 --> 00:18:36,181
Ahh.

360
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:36,722
Ow!

361
00:18:41,647 --> 00:18:43,247
And so I'm the one.

362
00:18:43,347 --> 00:18:46,747
After I spilled your sauce,
I concocted a new one.

363
00:18:46,847 --> 00:18:49,581
Look, Ukyo, what
Ranma really means

364
00:18:49,681 --> 00:18:53,481
is that he was being nice to you
because he was feeling guilty.

365
00:18:53,581 --> 00:18:54,814
Ranma.

366
00:18:54,914 --> 00:18:58,481
Hey, if you want to kick me
a few times, go right ahead.

367
00:19:07,181 --> 00:19:10,681
--[sigh] Oh, you
poor little thing.

368
00:19:10,781 --> 00:19:13,314
It was Akane who put you up
to this, wasn't it, Ranma?

369
00:19:13,414 --> 00:19:14,181
Huh?

370
00:19:14,281 --> 00:19:14,947
Huh?

371
00:19:15,047 --> 00:19:16,081
No.

372
00:19:16,181 --> 00:19:18,514
It's not like-- what I
mean is, Akane never--

373
00:19:18,614 --> 00:19:20,647
I just knew you
were behind this.

374
00:19:20,747 --> 00:19:22,047
What do you mean?

375
00:19:22,147 --> 00:19:25,214
If you think Ranma's
just going to run back,

376
00:19:25,314 --> 00:19:27,347
you're in for a
real disappointment.

377
00:19:27,447 --> 00:19:30,381
I'll do whatever it takes
to protect what's mine.

378
00:19:30,481 --> 00:19:31,881
Why would I--

379
00:19:31,981 --> 00:19:33,214
Yeah, and I'm not lying!

380
00:19:33,314 --> 00:19:34,147
Just hold on.

381
00:19:34,247 --> 00:19:37,114
Huh?

382
00:19:37,214 --> 00:19:39,314
It's time you
told her the truth.

383
00:19:39,414 --> 00:19:41,214
I don't get it.

384
00:19:41,314 --> 00:19:44,614
Ranma, Akane, you
both know you haven't

385
00:19:44,714 --> 00:19:46,614
told her the entire story.

386
00:19:46,714 --> 00:19:47,681
Huh?

387
00:19:47,781 --> 00:19:49,647
But Nabiki, we just
told her everything.

388
00:19:49,747 --> 00:19:51,281
OK, Ukyo.

389
00:19:51,381 --> 00:19:52,614
Here's the deal.

390
00:19:52,714 --> 00:19:55,914
You probably already knew
these two were engaged,

391
00:19:56,014 --> 00:19:58,114
but here's the part
you don't know.

392
00:20:02,914 --> 00:20:04,581
Your attention!

393
00:20:04,681 --> 00:20:09,214
Our happy couple are,
in fact, married!

394
00:20:09,314 --> 00:20:09,947
It's the truth.

395
00:20:10,047 --> 00:20:12,981
Oh, my.

396
00:20:13,081 --> 00:20:14,047
Huh?

397
00:20:14,147 --> 00:20:14,581
Huh?

398
00:20:14,681 --> 00:20:15,381
We're what?

399
00:20:15,481 --> 00:20:17,581
[screaming]

400
00:20:17,681 --> 00:20:19,081
Come on, go along
with the program.

401
00:20:19,181 --> 00:20:21,247
What have you got to lose?

402
00:20:21,347 --> 00:20:22,347
You're right.

403
00:20:22,447 --> 00:20:23,781
I've got nothing to lose.

404
00:20:23,881 --> 00:20:25,814
I'm so happy for you two!

405
00:20:29,381 --> 00:20:30,947
I'm so sorry, Ukyo.

406
00:20:31,047 --> 00:20:32,781
We should have told you.

407
00:20:32,881 --> 00:20:33,322
Huh?

408
00:20:36,281 --> 00:20:36,722
Lies!

409
00:20:36,781 --> 00:20:37,214
Lies!

410
00:20:37,214 --> 00:20:37,747
Lies!

411
00:20:37,847 --> 00:20:38,647
They're all lies!

412
00:20:41,914 --> 00:20:44,247
We can't hide the
truth anymore, darling.

413
00:20:44,347 --> 00:20:46,147
Have you gone nuts?

414
00:20:46,247 --> 00:20:48,914
[crying]

415
00:20:49,014 --> 00:20:49,581
Akane!

416
00:20:49,681 --> 00:20:52,847
Just play along, OK?

417
00:20:52,947 --> 00:20:54,714
OK, I will.

418
00:20:54,814 --> 00:20:57,281
I mean, I'd do anything to
help you get out of this jam.

419
00:20:57,381 --> 00:20:58,847
To help me out of this jam?

420
00:20:58,947 --> 00:20:59,388
Huh?

421
00:20:59,447 --> 00:21:01,614
Hm?

422
00:21:01,714 --> 00:21:04,214
So just what are you
two talking about?

423
00:21:04,314 --> 00:21:07,614
Well, we're just
your average couple.

424
00:21:07,714 --> 00:21:08,814
And we had a little argument.

425
00:21:08,914 --> 00:21:09,447
Oh, darling.

426
00:21:09,547 --> 00:21:09,988
Would you stop it?

427
00:21:10,047 --> 00:21:11,747
[laughter]

428
00:21:11,847 --> 00:21:14,247
I get it.

429
00:21:14,347 --> 00:21:15,747
Aren't you two cute?

430
00:21:15,847 --> 00:21:16,614
Shut up.

431
00:21:16,714 --> 00:21:20,081
I'm so happy for you.

432
00:21:20,181 --> 00:21:21,214
Oh, Akane.

433
00:21:21,314 --> 00:21:23,214
How I've waited for this day.

434
00:21:30,014 --> 00:21:31,847
UKYO (VOICEOVER):
I'm not backing down

435
00:21:31,947 --> 00:21:34,647
until I can expose
them of their charade.

436
00:21:40,647 --> 00:21:42,514
[theme song]

437
00:23:16,648 --> 00:23:18,515
AKANE (VOICEOVER): He's
a make believe husband,

438
00:23:18,615 --> 00:23:20,182
and I'm a make believe wife.

439
00:23:20,282 --> 00:23:23,382
Oh, how long are we gonna
have to keep this up!

440
00:23:23,482 --> 00:23:26,548
Next time on Ranma 1/2,
Ukyo's Secret Sauce, Part Two.

441
00:23:26,648 --> 00:23:28,715
We'll see you there!

